{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019Rds7PCzdcfTgsXqBgJUCS","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Taunt Bet - Capability Baseline\n2\t\n3\t> Temporary status note: `docs/SCOPE.md` is currently out of date during active replanning.\n4\t> Treat implementation, active game/backend specs, `docs/DECISIONS.md`, and `docs/DESIGN_REFERENCE.md` as the current source of truth until this document is rewritten.\n5\t> For now, this file should be considered informational only and may lag behind reality.\n6\t\n7\tNon-custodial P2P gaming platform on Solana. This document captures current implementation boundaries, architectural constraints, and planning direction without release labels.\n8\t\n9\t---\n10\t\n11\t## 1) Product Focus\n12\t\n13\tCurrent platform priorities:\n14\t- Real, playable game loops with on-chain settlement\n15\t- Verifiable fairness for completed rounds/matches\n16\t- Reliable wallet-authenticated flows\n17\t- Basic player history and operational safety controls\n18\t\n19\tThis document is intentionally product-facing and avoids implementation-level details.\n20\t\n21\t---\n22\t\n23\t## 2) Current Capability Set\n24\t\n25\t### Core Platform Capabilities\n26\t- Wallet connection (normal Solana wallet flow)\n27\t- Non-custodial transaction flow for all financial actions\n28\t- Fairness verification experience for supported games\n29\t- Basic user profile/history views\n30\t- Operational controls (pause/resume, monitoring, incident response)\n31\t\n32\t### Not Implemented in Current Baseline\n33\t- Internal custodial balance model\n34\t- Multichain support\n35\t- Token utility and token-gated mechanics\n36\t- Referral and creator monetization systems\n37\t- Full social layer (global chat rewards, advanced social graph)\n38\t\n39\t### Planned Backlog Themes (Unscheduled)\n40\t- Chat and social features\n41\t- Reward loops and progression expansion\n42\t- Additional games and game variants\n43\t- Extended wallet and account UX\n44\t\n45\t---\n46\t\n47\t## 3) Architecture Direction (Locked)\n48\t\n49\t### Core Decisions\n50\t- Chain: Solana\n51\t- Custody: Non-custodial\n52\t- Program model: Standard Anchor programs (per-game + shared crate, see `docs/specs/004-shared-infrastructure/spec.md`)\n53\t- Wallet approach: normal wallets first, embedded wallet support evaluated later\n54\t\n55\t### Explicit Constraint\n56\t- Do not build temporary architecture with planned rewrite.\n57\t- Stay on a single architecture path: program-per-game + shared Rust crate (`solana/shared/`). See `docs/DESIGN_REFERENCE.md`.\n58\t\n59\t---\n60\t\n61\t## 4) Trust Boundaries\n62\t\n63\t### On-Chain Source of Truth\n64\t- All money movement\n65\t- Round settlement outcomes\n66\t- Payout eligibility and claim state\n67\t\n68\t### Off-Chain Responsibilities\n69\t- Read models and indexing for UX/performance\n70\t- Profile/history aggregation\n71\t- Backend-assisted fairness services (secret generation, partial-sign create flows, settlement workers, verification endpoints)\n72\t- Fairness presentation and verification UX\n73\t- Real-time coordination where needed for UX\n74\t\n75\t### Rule\n76\t- If it changes user funds or determines payouts, it must be validated on-chain.\n77\t\n78\t---\n79\t\n80\t## 5) Active Game Coverage\n81\t\n82\t### Jackpot (Lord of the RNGs)\n83\t- Multiplayer weighted-entry jackpot pool\n84\t- Backend-assisted hybrid fairness (commitment at create, public entropy capture at spin/start, automatic settlement)\n85\t- Timeout-protected refund fallback\n86\t- Public verification payloads plus on-chain settlement evidence\n87\t\n88\t### Close Call\n89\t- Pari-mutuel BTC price prediction (green/red binary)\n90\t- Pyth oracle pricing via Hermes REST API\n91\t- 30s betting window, automatic settlement\n92\t- Max 32 entries per side\n93\t\n94\t### Coinflip\n95\t- Match creation/join flow\n96\t- Backend-partially-signed create flow with wallet-authenticated requests\n97\t- Hybrid fairness outcome from revealed secret + future slot-hash entropy\n98\t- Automatic settlement with timeout-protected refund fallback\n99\t- Public verification payloads plus on-chain settlement evidence\n100\t\n101\t### Shared Game Requirements\n102\t- Idempotent action handling\n103\t- Replay protection for signed actions\n104\t- Clear error states for failed transactions\n105\t- Devnet-first validation before production rollout\n106\t\n107\t---\n108\t\n109\t## 6) Functional Baseline\n110\t\n111\t- Users can connect wallets and perform game actions\n112\t- All financial interactions are on-chain\n113\t- Coinflip and Lord of the RNGs are playable end-to-end\n114\t- Users can verify fairness for completed rounds/matches\n115\t- Users can view basic profile and recent history\n116\t- Operators can pause/resume games\n117\t\n118\t---\n119\t\n120\t## 7) Non-Functional Baseline\n121\t\n122\t- Reliability: stable under expected load\n123\t- Observability: errors and key events are visible\n124\t- Security baseline: rate limiting, validation, abuse protections\n125\t- UX baseline: clear transaction state feedback and recovery paths\n126\t- Operational readiness: incident checklist and rollback procedure\n127\t\n128\t---\n129\t\n130\t## 8) Workstreams\n131\t\n132\t### Workstream A: Core Game Reliability\n133\t- Keep Coinflip and Lord of the RNGs robust end-to-end\n134\t- Maintain fairness verification and settlement correctness\n135\t- Continue devnet and local lifecycle validation\n136\t\n137\t### Workstream B: Player Data and UX Hardening\n138\t- Improve profile/history accuracy and completeness\n139\t- Strengthen wallet and transaction UX\n140\t- Improve error handling and recovery paths\n141\t\n142\t### Workstream C: Operations and Safety\n143\t- Keep pause/resume and incident handling reliable\n144\t- Improve monitoring and alerting\n145\t- Maintain rollback and operator runbook quality\n146\t\n147\t---\n148\t\n149\t## 9) Readiness Checklist\n150\t\n151\t### Functional\n152\t- [ ] Wallet connection works across supported wallet paths\n153\t- [ ] Lord of the RNGs playable end-to-end with real settlement path\n154\t- [ ] Coinflip playable end-to-end with real settlement path\n155\t- [ ] Fairness verification works for Lord of the RNGs\n156\t- [ ] Fairness verification works for Coinflip\n157\t- [ ] Basic profile/history available and accurate\n158\t\n159\t### Security and Integrity\n160\t- [ ] On-chain payout invariants validated\n161\t- [ ] Idempotency and replay protections validated\n162\t- [ ] Critical abuse paths mitigated\n163\t- [ ] Emergency pause tested\n164\t\n165\t### Operational\n166\t- [ ] Monitoring and error reporting active\n167\t- [ ] Incident and rollback playbook documented\n168\t- [ ] Devnet soak tests completed\n169\t\n170\t---\n171\t\n172\t## 10) Risks and Mitigations\n173\t\n174\t### Risk: Uncontrolled feature expansion\n175\t- Mitigation: Require explicit decision records for major product shifts\n176\t\n177\t### Risk: Fairness complexity in multiplayer mechanics\n178\t- Mitigation: Keep acceptance checks explicit for entry weighting, winner selection, settlement, and public verification\n179\t\n180\t### Risk: Integration drift across docs and code\n181\t- Mitigation: Keep architecture and workflow defaults centralized in `docs/DECISIONS.md`, `docs/WORKFLOW.md`, and this baseline file\n182\t\n183\t### Risk: Wallet UX friction\n184\t- Mitigation: Prioritize stable normal wallet flows and clear transaction feedback\n185\t\n186\t---\n187\t\n188\t## 11) Success Metrics\n189\t\n190\tPrimary:\n191\t- Successful completion rate of game rounds/matches\n192\t- Settlement correctness and claim success rate\n193\t- Fairness verification usage and pass rate\n194\t- Critical error rate within acceptable threshold\n195\t\n196\tSecondary:\n197\t- Early retention and repeat play behavior\n198\t- Time-to-complete for core game loops\n199\t\n200\t---\n201\t\n202\t## 12) Governance\n203\t\n204\t- Temporary override: this document is currently non-authoritative while replanning is in progress and should be ignored when it conflicts with implementation or newer decision/spec docs.\n205\t- Until `docs/SCOPE.md` is rewritten, use implementation, active specs, `docs/DECISIONS.md`, and `docs/DESIGN_REFERENCE.md` as the operational source of truth.\n206\t- New features require explicit decision records before broad rollout.\n207\t- Architecture model changes require a dedicated decision memo.\n208\t\n209\t---\n210\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b2d95d4b-db07-48d6-a5bf-2a0c1dc6d3ff","uuid":"a4df5f7a-03eb-4ccf-9c76-8ffbc11065e3","timestamp":"2026-04-04T07:57:28.977Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/SCOPE.md","content":"# Taunt Bet - Capability Baseline\n\n> Temporary status note: `docs/SCOPE.md` is currently out of date during active replanning.\n> Treat implementation, active game/backend specs, `docs/DECISIONS.md`, and `docs/DESIGN_REFERENCE.md` as the current source of truth until this document is rewritten.\n> For now, this file should be considered informational only and may lag behind reality.\n\nNon-custodial P2P gaming platform on Solana. This document captures current implementation boundaries, architectural constraints, and planning direction without release labels.\n\n---\n\n## 1) Product Focus\n\nCurrent platform priorities:\n- Real, playable game loops with on-chain settlement\n- Verifiable fairness for completed rounds/matches\n- Reliable wallet-authenticated flows\n- Basic player history and operational safety controls\n\nThis document is intentionally product-facing and avoids implementation-level details.\n\n---\n\n## 2) Current Capability Set\n\n### Core Platform Capabilities\n- Wallet connection (normal Solana wallet flow)\n- Non-custodial transaction flow for all financial actions\n- Fairness verification experience for supported games\n- Basic user profile/history views\n- Operational controls (pause/resume, monitoring, incident response)\n\n### Not Implemented in Current Baseline\n- Internal custodial balance model\n- Multichain support\n- Token utility and token-gated mechanics\n- Referral and creator monetization systems\n- Full social layer (global chat rewards, advanced social graph)\n\n### Planned Backlog Themes (Unscheduled)\n- Chat and social features\n- Reward loops and progression expansion\n- Additional games and game variants\n- Extended wallet and account UX\n\n---\n\n## 3) Architecture Direction (Locked)\n\n### Core Decisions\n- Chain: Solana\n- Custody: Non-custodial\n- Program model: Standard Anchor programs (per-game + shared crate, see `docs/specs/004-shared-infrastructure/spec.md`)\n- Wallet approach: normal wallets first, embedded wallet support evaluated later\n\n### Explicit Constraint\n- Do not build temporary architecture with planned rewrite.\n- Stay on a single architecture path: program-per-game + shared Rust crate (`solana/shared/`). See `docs/DESIGN_REFERENCE.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 4) Trust Boundaries\n\n### On-Chain Source of Truth\n- All money movement\n- Round settlement outcomes\n- Payout eligibility and claim state\n\n### Off-Chain Responsibilities\n- Read models and indexing for UX/performance\n- Profile/history aggregation\n- Backend-assisted fairness services (secret generation, partial-sign create flows, settlement workers, verification endpoints)\n- Fairness presentation and verification UX\n- Real-time coordination where needed for UX\n\n### Rule\n- If it changes user funds or determines payouts, it must be validated on-chain.\n\n---\n\n## 5) Active Game Coverage\n\n### Jackpot (Lord of the RNGs)\n- Multiplayer weighted-entry jackpot pool\n- Backend-assisted hybrid fairness (commitment at create, public entropy capture at spin/start, automatic settlement)\n- Timeout-protected refund fallback\n- Public verification payloads plus on-chain settlement evidence\n\n### Close Call\n- Pari-mutuel BTC price prediction (green/red binary)\n- Pyth oracle pricing via Hermes REST API\n- 30s betting window, automatic settlement\n- Max 32 entries per side\n\n### Coinflip\n- Match creation/join flow\n- Backend-partially-signed create flow with wallet-authenticated requests\n- Hybrid fairness outcome from revealed secret + future slot-hash entropy\n- Automatic settlement with timeout-protected refund fallback\n- Public verification payloads plus on-chain settlement evidence\n\n### Shared Game Requirements\n- Idempotent action handling\n- Replay protection for signed actions\n- Clear error states for failed transactions\n- Devnet-first validation before production rollout\n\n---\n\n## 6) Functional Baseline\n\n- Users can connect wallets and perform game actions\n- All financial interactions are on-chain\n- Coinflip and Lord of the RNGs are playable end-to-end\n- Users can verify fairness for completed rounds/matches\n- Users can view basic profile and recent history\n- Operators can pause/resume games\n\n---\n\n## 7) Non-Functional Baseline\n\n- Reliability: stable under expected load\n- Observability: errors and key events are visible\n- Security baseline: rate limiting, validation, abuse protections\n- UX baseline: clear transaction state feedback and recovery paths\n- Operational readiness: incident checklist and rollback procedure\n\n---\n\n## 8) Workstreams\n\n### Workstream A: Core Game Reliability\n- Keep Coinflip and Lord of the RNGs robust end-to-end\n- Maintain fairness verification and settlement correctness\n- Continue devnet and local lifecycle validation\n\n### Workstream B: Player Data and UX Hardening\n- Improve profile/history accuracy and completeness\n- Strengthen wallet and transaction UX\n- Improve error handling and recovery paths\n\n### Workstream C: Operations and Safety\n- Keep pause/resume and incident handling reliable\n- Improve monitoring and alerting\n- Maintain rollback and operator runbook quality\n\n---\n\n## 9) Readiness Checklist\n\n### Functional\n- [ ] Wallet connection works across supported wallet paths\n- [ ] Lord of the RNGs playable end-to-end with real settlement path\n- [ ] Coinflip playable end-to-end with real settlement path\n- [ ] Fairness verification works for Lord of the RNGs\n- [ ] Fairness verification works for Coinflip\n- [ ] Basic profile/history available and accurate\n\n### Security and Integrity\n- [ ] On-chain payout invariants validated\n- [ ] Idempotency and replay protections validated\n- [ ] Critical abuse paths mitigated\n- [ ] Emergency pause tested\n\n### Operational\n- [ ] Monitoring and error reporting active\n- [ ] Incident and rollback playbook documented\n- [ ] Devnet soak tests completed\n\n---\n\n## 10) Risks and Mitigations\n\n### Risk: Uncontrolled feature expansion\n- Mitigation: Require explicit decision records for major product shifts\n\n### Risk: Fairness complexity in multiplayer mechanics\n- Mitigation: Keep acceptance checks explicit for entry weighting, winner selection, settlement, and public verification\n\n### Risk: Integration drift across docs and code\n- Mitigation: Keep architecture and workflow defaults centralized in `docs/DECISIONS.md`, `docs/WORKFLOW.md`, and this baseline file\n\n### Risk: Wallet UX friction\n- Mitigation: Prioritize stable normal wallet flows and clear transaction feedback\n\n---\n\n## 11) Success Metrics\n\nPrimary:\n- Successful completion rate of game rounds/matches\n- Settlement correctness and claim success rate\n- Fairness verification usage and pass rate\n- Critical error rate within acceptable threshold\n\nSecondary:\n- Early retention and repeat play behavior\n- Time-to-complete for core game loops\n\n---\n\n## 12) Governance\n\n- Temporary override: this document is currently non-authoritative while replanning is in progress and should be ignored when it conflicts with implementation or newer decision/spec docs.\n- Until `docs/SCOPE.md` is rewritten, use implementation, active specs, `docs/DECISIONS.md`, and `docs/DESIGN_REFERENCE.md` as the operational source of truth.\n- New features require explicit decision records before broad rollout.\n- Architecture model changes require a dedicated decision memo.\n\n---\n","numLines":210,"startLine":1,"totalLines":210}}}
