{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LuzYGPXM2z7gKXsYGKQZWA","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Specification: [400] Challenge Engine & Reward System\n2\t\n3\t## Meta\n4\t\n5\t| Field | Value |\n6\t|-------|-------|\n7\t| Status | Done |\n8\t| Priority | P1 |\n9\t| Track | Core |\n10\t| NR_OF_TRIES | 18 |\n11\t\n12\t---\n13\t\n14\t## Overview\n15\t\n16\tA backend service that gives players daily and weekly gameplay objectives, tracks progress automatically via game settlement events, awards points for wagering, drops loot crates with configurable probability, and runs scheduled Dogpile events with boosted multipliers. Every challenge drives lobby activity — no social media chores, no off-platform actions.\n17\t\n18\tThe system introduces three new primitives:\n19\t1. **Points** — earned passively per $ wagered (configurable rate). Pre-TGE allocation signal. Free to mint.\n20\t2. **Loot Crates** — random drops after settled games. Two types: points crates (free) and SOL crates (capped by reward-pool accounting).\n21\t3. **Reward Pool** — a configurable share of collected platform fees, tracked as an accounting ledger that caps and records SOL crate payouts.\n22\t\n23\tThe challenge engine is event-driven, plugging into the existing async event queue (spec 301). It receives `game.settled` events from the settlement workers, evaluates progress against active challenges, and emits reward-intent events for downstream handlers. Challenge evaluation stays separate from reward side-effects: `game.settled` advances progress and emits `reward.pool_fund`, `points.grant`, and `crate.drop`, while dedicated handlers perform pool accounting, point grants, crate recording, and SOL payouts.\n24\t\n25\t### Design Principles (from reference spec)\n26\t\n27\t1. **Every challenge must fill a lobby or make the platform more alive.** No off-platform actions.\n28\t2. **One progression number: points.** No XP, no levels, no badges, no cosmetics.\n29\t3. **Rewards are crates and points. That's it.** No shops, no catalogs.\n30\t\n31\t## User Stories\n32\t\n33\t- As a player, I want to see daily and weekly challenges so that I have concrete goals beyond individual games\n34\t- As a player, I want my challenge progress to update automatically when I play so that I don't need to claim or submit proof\n35\t- As a player, I want to earn points proportional to my wagered volume so that every game feels rewarding\n36\t- As a player, I want a chance at loot crates after each game so that settlements have an extra moment of excitement\n37\t- As a player, I want a bonus reward for completing all my daily challenges so that I'm motivated to finish the set\n38\t- As a new player, I want guided onboarding challenges so that I learn the platform's game types and mechanics\n39\t- As a player, I want Dogpile events to boost my point earnings so that I'm motivated to play during peak hours\n40\t- As an operator, I want to configure point rates, crate drop rates, and reward pool share without redeploying so that I can tune economics live\n41\t- As an operator, I want lightweight anti-abuse signals so that obviously suspicious reward activity can be reviewed without over-engineering M1\n42\t\n43\t---\n44\t\n45\t## Capability Alignment\n46\t\n47\t- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 \"Not Implemented\" -> \"Reward loops and progression expansion\"; Section 8 Workstream A (core game reliability provides the settlement events this consumes)\n48\t- **Current baseline fit**: Not Implemented\n49\t- **Planning bucket**: Core (extends the game loop)\n50\t- **Reference doc**: `docs/references/challenge-engine-spec.md` (full design research)\n51\t\n52\t## Required Context Files\n53\t\n54\t- `docs/specs/301-async-event-queue/spec.md` — event queue we plug into\n55\t- `docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md` — pattern for event handlers, DB conventions\n56\t- `backend/services/backend/src/queue/` — event queue implementation\n57\t- `backend/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` — settlement hot path (emits new events)\n58\t- `backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` — DB client and query patterns\n59\t- `backend/services/backend/migrations/007_game_entries.sql` — game_entries schema (data source for adapters)\n60\t- `docs/DESIGN_REFERENCE.md` — trust model, fee structure (500 bps)\n61\t\n62\t## Contract Files\n63\t\n64\t- No existing mocks — new system\n65\t- API contract defined in FR-14 below\n66\t- Event contracts defined in FR-1\n67\t\n68\t---\n69\t\n70\t## System Invariants\n71\t\n72\t1. **Points are free to mint.** No budget constraint. Points never come from the reward pool.\n73\t2. **Reward pool is accounting-only in M1.** All on-chain fees still settle to the single treasury; `reward_pool` is an off-chain ledger that tracks how much of that fee flow is reserved for crate economics.\n74\t3. **Reward pool balance cannot go negative.** If pool < `sol_crate_min_value`, SOL crate drops are suppressed until the pool recovers.\n75\t4. **Challenge progress is idempotent.** Processing the same `game.settled` event twice produces the same progress state.\n76\t5. **Reward side-effects are idempotent.** Pool funding, point grants, crate creation, and SOL payouts must dedupe on domain keys from the payload, never `event_queue.id`.\n77\t6. **Settlement must never block on challenge processing.** Challenge evaluation is async (via event queue). Settlement latency is unaffected.\n78\t7. **All monetary values in lamports (BIGINT).** SOL conversion only at display boundaries.\n79\t8. **Operator config changes take effect immediately.** No redeploy, no restart. Read from `reward_config` table on each evaluation.\n80\t\n81\t---\n82\t\n83\t## Functional Requirements\n84\t\n85\t### FR-1: Game Settlement Event Emission\n86\t\n87\tExtend the settlement workers to emit a `game.settled` event into the async event queue for every settled game. This is the foundation all downstream processing depends on.\n88\t\n89\t**Event payload:**\n90\t\n91\t```typescript\n92\t{\n93\t  roundId: string;          // match_id (hex)\n94\t  roundPda: string;         // on-chain PDA\n95\t  game: \"coinflip\" | \"lord\" | \"closecall\";\n96\t  players: Array<{\n97\t    userId: string;\n98\t    wallet: string;\n99\t    amountLamports: string; // bigint as string\n100\t    isWinner: boolean | null; // null = refund\n101\t    payoutLamports: string;\n102\t    isCreator: boolean;\n103\t  }>;\n104\t  feeLamports: string;\n105\t  settledAt: string;        // ISO 8601\n106\t}\n107\t```\n108\t\n109\tThe event MUST be emitted within the same DB transaction as the settlement write (same pattern as referral earnings recording).\n110\t\n111\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n112\t- [ ] `game.settled` event type added to `EventTypes` in `event-types.ts`\n113\t- [ ] `settle-tx.ts` emits `game.settled` within the settlement transaction for coinflip rounds\n114\t- [ ] `settle-tx.ts` emits `game.settled` within the settlement transaction for lord (jackpot) rounds\n115\t- [ ] `closecall-clock.ts` emits `game.settled` within the settlement transaction for closecall rounds\n116\t- [ ] Event payload matches the schema above (all fields present, amounts as string-encoded lamports)\n117\t- [ ] Existing settlement latency is not measurably affected (event is a single INSERT, no blocking)\n118\t- [ ] Duplicate settlement retries may enqueue duplicate `game.settled` rows safely because downstream handlers dedupe on domain keys, not `event_queue.id`\n119\t\n120\t---\n121\t\n122\t### FR-2: Challenge Engine Data Model\n123\t\n124\tDatabase schema for challenges, assignments, and progress tracking.\n125\t\n126\t**Tables:**\n127\t\n128\t```sql\n129\t-- Operator-tunable reward/economy parameters\n130\tCREATE TABLE reward_config (\n131\t  key         TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n132\t  value       TEXT NOT NULL,           -- JSON-encoded value\n133\t  updated_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n134\t);\n135\t\n136\t-- Player point balances and lifetime stats\n137\tCREATE TABLE player_points (\n138\t  user_id             TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n139\t  wallet              TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n140\t  balance             BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,        -- current spendable\n141\t  lifetime_earned     BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,        -- monotonic, never decreases\n142\t  updated_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n143\t);\n144\t\n145\t-- Immutable point grant ledger (source of truth for history + idempotency)\n146\tCREATE TABLE point_grants (\n147\t  id                  BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n148\t  user_id             TEXT NOT NULL,\n149\t  wallet              TEXT NOT NULL,\n150\t  source_type         TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (source_type IN ('wager', 'challenge_completed', 'bonus_completed', 'crate_points')),\n151\t  source_id           TEXT NOT NULL,                    -- round_id, assignment_id, bonus_completion_id, crate_drop_id\n152\t  amount              BIGINT NOT NULL,\n153\t  metadata            JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n154\t  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n155\t  UNIQUE (user_id, source_type, source_id)\n156\t);\n157\t\n158\tCREATE INDEX idx_point_grants_user_created ON point_grants (user_id, created_at DESC);\n159\t\n160\t-- Reward pool accounting (single row, updated atomically)\n161\tCREATE TABLE reward_pool (\n162\t  id                  INT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT 1 CHECK (id = 1),  -- singleton, accounting-only ledger\n163\t  balance_lamports    BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n164\t  lifetime_funded     BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,    -- total fees -> pool\n165\t  lifetime_paid       BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,    -- total crate payouts\n166\t  updated_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n167\t);\n168\t\n169\t-- Append-only pool funding ledger for idempotent reward_pool_fund handling\n170\tCREATE TABLE reward_pool_fundings (\n171\t  id                  BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n172\t  round_id            TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,         -- one funding record per settled round\n173\t  fee_lamports        BIGINT NOT NULL,\n174\t  funded_lamports     BIGINT NOT NULL,\n175\t  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n176\t);\n177\t\n178\t-- Campaign container (Daily, Weekly, Onboarding, Dogpile)\n179\tCREATE TABLE campaigns (\n180\t  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n181\t  name            TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n182\t  campaign_type   TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (campaign_type IN ('daily', 'weekly', 'onboarding', 'dogpile')),\n183\t  starts_at       TIMESTAMPTZ,                  -- NULL = always active\n184\t  ends_at         TIMESTAMPTZ,                  -- NULL = no end\n185\t  is_active       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true,\n186\t  config          JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',  -- type-specific config (e.g., dogpile multiplier)\n187\t  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n188\t);\n189\t\n190\t-- Challenge template definitions (data, not code)\n191\tCREATE TABLE challenges (\n192\t  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n193\t  campaign_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES campaigns(id),\n194\t  title           TEXT NOT NULL,\n195\t  description     TEXT,\n196\t  action          TEXT NOT NULL,                 -- M1 adapter type: game_won, game_completed, lobby_filled\n197\t  scope           TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'any' CHECK (scope IN ('any', 'coinflip', 'lord', 'closecall')),\n198\t  condition       TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'count', -- M1: count, unique_game_types\n199\t  threshold       INT NOT NULL,                  -- target value\n200\t  reward_type     TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (reward_type IN ('points', 'crate')),"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b2d95d4b-db07-48d6-a5bf-2a0c1dc6d3ff","uuid":"ce8d8864-e98e-4930-a8f8-45e0c45d9803","timestamp":"2026-04-04T07:57:34.590Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/400-challenge-engine/spec.md","content":"# Specification: [400] Challenge Engine & Reward System\n\n## Meta\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Status | Done |\n| Priority | P1 |\n| Track | Core |\n| NR_OF_TRIES | 18 |\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nA backend service that gives players daily and weekly gameplay objectives, tracks progress automatically via game settlement events, awards points for wagering, drops loot crates with configurable probability, and runs scheduled Dogpile events with boosted multipliers. Every challenge drives lobby activity — no social media chores, no off-platform actions.\n\nThe system introduces three new primitives:\n1. **Points** — earned passively per $ wagered (configurable rate). Pre-TGE allocation signal. Free to mint.\n2. **Loot Crates** — random drops after settled games. Two types: points crates (free) and SOL crates (capped by reward-pool accounting).\n3. **Reward Pool** — a configurable share of collected platform fees, tracked as an accounting ledger that caps and records SOL crate payouts.\n\nThe challenge engine is event-driven, plugging into the existing async event queue (spec 301). It receives `game.settled` events from the settlement workers, evaluates progress against active challenges, and emits reward-intent events for downstream handlers. Challenge evaluation stays separate from reward side-effects: `game.settled` advances progress and emits `reward.pool_fund`, `points.grant`, and `crate.drop`, while dedicated handlers perform pool accounting, point grants, crate recording, and SOL payouts.\n\n### Design Principles (from reference spec)\n\n1. **Every challenge must fill a lobby or make the platform more alive.** No off-platform actions.\n2. **One progression number: points.** No XP, no levels, no badges, no cosmetics.\n3. **Rewards are crates and points. That's it.** No shops, no catalogs.\n\n## User Stories\n\n- As a player, I want to see daily and weekly challenges so that I have concrete goals beyond individual games\n- As a player, I want my challenge progress to update automatically when I play so that I don't need to claim or submit proof\n- As a player, I want to earn points proportional to my wagered volume so that every game feels rewarding\n- As a player, I want a chance at loot crates after each game so that settlements have an extra moment of excitement\n- As a player, I want a bonus reward for completing all my daily challenges so that I'm motivated to finish the set\n- As a new player, I want guided onboarding challenges so that I learn the platform's game types and mechanics\n- As a player, I want Dogpile events to boost my point earnings so that I'm motivated to play during peak hours\n- As an operator, I want to configure point rates, crate drop rates, and reward pool share without redeploying so that I can tune economics live\n- As an operator, I want lightweight anti-abuse signals so that obviously suspicious reward activity can be reviewed without over-engineering M1\n\n---\n\n## Capability Alignment\n\n- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 \"Not Implemented\" -> \"Reward loops and progression expansion\"; Section 8 Workstream A (core game reliability provides the settlement events this consumes)\n- **Current baseline fit**: Not Implemented\n- **Planning bucket**: Core (extends the game loop)\n- **Reference doc**: `docs/references/challenge-engine-spec.md` (full design research)\n\n## Required Context Files\n\n- `docs/specs/301-async-event-queue/spec.md` — event queue we plug into\n- `docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md` — pattern for event handlers, DB conventions\n- `backend/services/backend/src/queue/` — event queue implementation\n- `backend/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` — settlement hot path (emits new events)\n- `backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` — DB client and query patterns\n- `backend/services/backend/migrations/007_game_entries.sql` — game_entries schema (data source for adapters)\n- `docs/DESIGN_REFERENCE.md` — trust model, fee structure (500 bps)\n\n## Contract Files\n\n- No existing mocks — new system\n- API contract defined in FR-14 below\n- Event contracts defined in FR-1\n\n---\n\n## System Invariants\n\n1. **Points are free to mint.** No budget constraint. Points never come from the reward pool.\n2. **Reward pool is accounting-only in M1.** All on-chain fees still settle to the single treasury; `reward_pool` is an off-chain ledger that tracks how much of that fee flow is reserved for crate economics.\n3. **Reward pool balance cannot go negative.** If pool < `sol_crate_min_value`, SOL crate drops are suppressed until the pool recovers.\n4. **Challenge progress is idempotent.** Processing the same `game.settled` event twice produces the same progress state.\n5. **Reward side-effects are idempotent.** Pool funding, point grants, crate creation, and SOL payouts must dedupe on domain keys from the payload, never `event_queue.id`.\n6. **Settlement must never block on challenge processing.** Challenge evaluation is async (via event queue). Settlement latency is unaffected.\n7. **All monetary values in lamports (BIGINT).** SOL conversion only at display boundaries.\n8. **Operator config changes take effect immediately.** No redeploy, no restart. Read from `reward_config` table on each evaluation.\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n### FR-1: Game Settlement Event Emission\n\nExtend the settlement workers to emit a `game.settled` event into the async event queue for every settled game. This is the foundation all downstream processing depends on.\n\n**Event payload:**\n\n```typescript\n{\n  roundId: string;          // match_id (hex)\n  roundPda: string;         // on-chain PDA\n  game: \"coinflip\" | \"lord\" | \"closecall\";\n  players: Array<{\n    userId: string;\n    wallet: string;\n    amountLamports: string; // bigint as string\n    isWinner: boolean | null; // null = refund\n    payoutLamports: string;\n    isCreator: boolean;\n  }>;\n  feeLamports: string;\n  settledAt: string;        // ISO 8601\n}\n```\n\nThe event MUST be emitted within the same DB transaction as the settlement write (same pattern as referral earnings recording).\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] `game.settled` event type added to `EventTypes` in `event-types.ts`\n- [ ] `settle-tx.ts` emits `game.settled` within the settlement transaction for coinflip rounds\n- [ ] `settle-tx.ts` emits `game.settled` within the settlement transaction for lord (jackpot) rounds\n- [ ] `closecall-clock.ts` emits `game.settled` within the settlement transaction for closecall rounds\n- [ ] Event payload matches the schema above (all fields present, amounts as string-encoded lamports)\n- [ ] Existing settlement latency is not measurably affected (event is a single INSERT, no blocking)\n- [ ] Duplicate settlement retries may enqueue duplicate `game.settled` rows safely because downstream handlers dedupe on domain keys, not `event_queue.id`\n\n---\n\n### FR-2: Challenge Engine Data Model\n\nDatabase schema for challenges, assignments, and progress tracking.\n\n**Tables:**\n\n```sql\n-- Operator-tunable reward/economy parameters\nCREATE TABLE reward_config (\n  key         TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  value       TEXT NOT NULL,           -- JSON-encoded value\n  updated_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n\n-- Player point balances and lifetime stats\nCREATE TABLE player_points (\n  user_id             TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  wallet              TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  balance             BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,        -- current spendable\n  lifetime_earned     BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,        -- monotonic, never decreases\n  updated_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n\n-- Immutable point grant ledger (source of truth for history + idempotency)\nCREATE TABLE point_grants (\n  id                  BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id             TEXT NOT NULL,\n  wallet              TEXT NOT NULL,\n  source_type         TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (source_type IN ('wager', 'challenge_completed', 'bonus_completed', 'crate_points')),\n  source_id           TEXT NOT NULL,                    -- round_id, assignment_id, bonus_completion_id, crate_drop_id\n  amount              BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  metadata            JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  UNIQUE (user_id, source_type, source_id)\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_point_grants_user_created ON point_grants (user_id, created_at DESC);\n\n-- Reward pool accounting (single row, updated atomically)\nCREATE TABLE reward_pool (\n  id                  INT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT 1 CHECK (id = 1),  -- singleton, accounting-only ledger\n  balance_lamports    BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  lifetime_funded     BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,    -- total fees -> pool\n  lifetime_paid       BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,    -- total crate payouts\n  updated_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n\n-- Append-only pool funding ledger for idempotent reward_pool_fund handling\nCREATE TABLE reward_pool_fundings (\n  id                  BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  round_id            TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,         -- one funding record per settled round\n  fee_lamports        BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  funded_lamports     BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n\n-- Campaign container (Daily, Weekly, Onboarding, Dogpile)\nCREATE TABLE campaigns (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  name            TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  campaign_type   TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (campaign_type IN ('daily', 'weekly', 'onboarding', 'dogpile')),\n  starts_at       TIMESTAMPTZ,                  -- NULL = always active\n  ends_at         TIMESTAMPTZ,                  -- NULL = no end\n  is_active       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true,\n  config          JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',  -- type-specific config (e.g., dogpile multiplier)\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n\n-- Challenge template definitions (data, not code)\nCREATE TABLE challenges (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  campaign_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES campaigns(id),\n  title           TEXT NOT NULL,\n  description     TEXT,\n  action          TEXT NOT NULL,                 -- M1 adapter type: game_won, game_completed, lobby_filled\n  scope           TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'any' CHECK (scope IN ('any', 'coinflip', 'lord', 'closecall')),\n  condition       TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'count', -- M1: count, unique_game_types\n  threshold       INT NOT NULL,                  -- target value\n  reward_type     TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (reward_type IN ('points', 'crate')),","numLines":200,"startLine":1,"totalLines":926}}}
