{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01D33K1LeLe4fFqTtZMyCSCg","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive inventory report.\n\n## Challenge Engine Implementation Inventory\n\n### 1. EVENT TYPES\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n\nDefined event type constants (lines 8-17):\n- `REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED` = \"referral.code_applied\"\n- `REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED` = \"referral.game_settled\"\n- `REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED` = \"referral.claim_requested\"\n- `GAME_SETTLED` = \"game.settled\"\n- `REWARD_POOL_FUND` = \"reward.pool_fund\"\n- `POINTS_GRANT` = \"points.grant\"\n- `CRATE_DROP` = \"crate.drop\"\n- `CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT` = \"crate.sol_payout\"\n\n---\n\n### 2. EVENT HANDLERS\n\n**Directory:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/`\n\n#### game-settled.ts (Line 142)\n- **Exported Function:** `createGameSettledHandler(deps: GameSettledDeps)`\n- **Helper Functions:**\n  - `getActiveAssignmentsWithChallenge()` (line 56)\n  - `insertProgressEvent()` (line 85)\n  - `incrementAssignmentProgress()` (line 106)\n  - `markAssignmentCompleted()` (line 123)\n\n**Purpose:** Orchestrator for the challenge engine. Processes each player in a settled game event, evaluating challenge progress, emitting reward intents, and handling wager-based points + crate drops.\n\n#### challenge-adapters.ts (Line 144)\n- **Exported Function:** `getAdapter(action: string): VerificationAdapter` (line 144)\n- **Adapter Functions:**\n  - `gameCompletedAdapter()` (line 93) - Player participated in settled game\n  - `gameWonAdapter()` (line 106) - Player won a settled game\n  - `lobbyFilledAdapter()` (line 120) - Player created game that was filled and settled\n- **Helper:** `questEligible(player: GameSettledPlayer): boolean` (line 72)\n\n**Purpose:** Pure verification adapters that evaluate whether a game.settled event advances challenge progress. Quest eligibility gates skip refunded games.\n\n#### reward-pool-fund.ts (Line 70)\n- **Exported Function:** `createRewardPoolFundHandler(deps: RewardPoolFundDeps)`\n- **Helper Functions:**\n  - `readRewardConfig(db: Db, key: string)` (line 17)\n  - `insertPoolFunding()` (line 31)\n  - `incrementRewardPool()` (line 49)\n\n**Purpose:** Allocates a share of game fees to the reward pool. Emitted once per settled round. Idempotent via UNIQUE(round_id).\n\n#### points-grant.ts (Line 89)\n- **Exported Function:** `createPointsGrantHandler(deps: PointsGrantDeps)`\n- **Helper Functions:**\n  - `insertPointGrant()` (line 24)\n  - `upsertPlayerPoints()` (line 46)\n  - `getActiveDogpileMultiplier()` (line 66)\n\n**Purpose:** Awards points to a player. Converts lamports → USD → points for wager-based grants, applies active Dogpile multiplier. Pre-calculated grants supported. Idempotent via UNIQUE(user_id, source_type, source_id).\n\n#### crate-drop.ts (Line 98)\n- **Exported Function:** `createCrateDropHandler(deps: CrateDropDeps)`\n- **Helper Functions:**\n  - `lockAndReadRewardPool()` (line 35)\n  - `decrementRewardPool()` (line 54)\n  - `insertCrateDrop()` (line 71)\n\n**Purpose:** Rolls for loot crate drops after settled game. Two paths: SOL crate (higher value, lower probability) or Points crate. Idempotent via UNIQUE(user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id).\n\n#### completion-bonus.ts (Line 91)\n- **Exported Function:** `checkCompletionBonus(db, userId, wallet, periodKey, campaignId)`\n- **Helper Functions:**\n  - `getCompletionBonuses()` (line 28)\n  - `countCompletedAssignments()` (line 43)\n  - `insertBonusCompletion()` (line 64)\n\n**Purpose:** Checks and awards completion bonuses after assignment completion (e.g., complete 3 daily challenges → bonus crate). Called from game.settled handler within completion transaction.\n\n#### onboarding-chain.ts (Line 74)\n- **Exported Function:** `advanceOnboardingChain(db, userId, completedChallengeId, periodKey)`\n- **Helper Functions:**\n  - `getNextOnboardingStep()` (line 29)\n  - `createAssignment()` (line 47)\n\n**Purpose:** Auto-assigns next onboarding step when a player completes an onboarding challenge. Onboarding challenges link via prerequisite_id for chaining.\n\n#### crate-sol-payout.ts (Line 68)\n- **Exported Function:** `createCrateSolPayoutHandler(deps: CrateSolPayoutDeps)`\n- **Helper Functions:**\n  - `loadCrateDropById()` (line 33)\n  - `updateCrateStatus()` (line 45)\n\n**Purpose:** Sends SOL to player wallet for SOL crate drops. Verifies status='pending', executes transfer, updates to 'granted' or 'failed'. Idempotent.\n\n#### referral-claim.ts (Line 31)\n- **Exported Function:** `createClaimHandler(deps: ClaimHandlerDeps)`\n\n**Purpose:** Processes referral.claim_requested events. Verifies balance, executes SOL transfer, records tx_signature. Transient errors marked 'error' (retryable), terminal failures marked 'failed' after MAX_CLAIM_RETRIES.\n\n---\n\n### 3. ROUTES\n\n**Directory:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/`\n\n#### challenges.ts (Line 305)\n- **Exported Function:** `createChallengeRoutes(deps: ChallengeRoutesDeps)`\n- **Endpoints:**\n  - `GET /mine` (line 309) - Active daily, weekly, onboarding challenges with lazy assignment\n  - `GET /mine/history` (line 497) - Paginated completed challenge assignments\n- **Helper Functions:**\n  - `dailyPeriodKey()` (line 71)\n  - `weeklyPeriodKey()` (line 77)\n  - `dailyResetsAt()` (line 88)\n  - `weeklyResetsAt()` (line 95)\n\n#### points.ts (Line 39)\n- **Exported Function:** `createPointsRoutes(deps: PointsRoutesDeps)`\n- **Endpoints:**\n  - `GET /mine` (line 44) - Current point balance + lifetime earned\n  - `GET /mine/history` (line 71) - Paginated point_grants ledger\n- **Also exported:** `createCrateRoutes(deps: PointsRoutesDeps)` (line 131)\n- **Endpoints:**\n  - `GET /mine` (line 136) - Paginated crate_drops history\n\n#### dogpile.ts (Line 34)\n- **Exported Function:** `createDogpileRoutes(deps: DogpileRoutesDeps)`\n- **Endpoints:**\n  - `GET /current` (line 39) - Active dogpile event, or next scheduled, or null\n  - `GET /schedule` (line 94) - Upcoming dogpile events ordered by starts_at\n\n#### admin.ts (Line 38)\n- **Exported Function:** `createAdminRoutes(deps: AdminRoutesDeps)`\n- **Endpoints:**\n  - `GET /reward-config` (line 52) - All config key-value pairs\n  - `PUT /reward-config/:key` (line 64) - Update single config value\n  - `GET /reward-pool` (line 86) - Current pool state\n  - `POST /campaigns` (line 115) - Create campaign\n  - `PUT /campaigns/:id` (line 158) - Update campaign\n  - `POST /challenges` (line 230) - Create challenge\n  - `PUT /challenges/:id` (line 308) - Update challenge\n  - `POST /dogpile` (line 421) - Schedule dogpile event\n  - `PUT /dogpile/:id` (line 487) - Cancel dogpile event\n  - `GET /dogpile` (line 544) - List dogpile events (optional status filter)\n\n#### health.ts (Line 18)\n- **Exported Function:** `createHealthRoutes(deps: HealthDeps)`\n- **Endpoints:**\n  - `GET /` (line 24) - Health endpoint with optional verbose flag\n\n#### internal.ts (Line 24)\n- **Exported Function:** `createInternalRoutes(deps: InternalRoutesDeps)`\n- **Endpoints:**\n  - `POST /reset-db` (line 28) - Drop tables and re-run migrations (dev-only)\n\n---\n\n### 4. WORKERS\n\n**Directory:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/worker/`\n\n#### settle-tx.ts\n- **Emits `game.settled`:**\n  - Line 442: Coinflip game settlement\n  - Line 729: Lord (jackpot) game settlement\n\n#### closecall-clock.ts\n- **Emits `game.settled`:**\n  - Line 611: Close Call game settlement (oracle-resolved)\n\n#### dogpile-worker.ts (Line 22)\n- **Exported Function:** `createDogpileWorker(deps: DogpileWorkerDeps): DogpileWorker`\n- **Key Method:** `tick()` (line 26)\n- **Handles:** Transitions `scheduled → active` and `active → ended` for dogpile_events\n- **Poll Interval:** Default 10 seconds (configurable)\n\n**Note:** dogpile-worker.ts does NOT handle dogpile in the settlement sense — it manages the lifecycle of Dogpile multiplier events based on time windows.\n\n---\n\n### 5. HANDLER REGISTRATION AND ROUTE MOUNTING\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n\n#### Handler Registration (Lines 212-242):\n```typescript\n// Line 214-215\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\n\n// Line 217-220\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.GAME_SETTLED,\n  createGameSettledHandler({ db }),\n);\n\n// Line 221-224\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REWARD_POOL_FUND,\n  createRewardPoolFundHandler({ db }),\n);\n\n// Line 225-234\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.POINTS_GRANT,\n  createPointsGrantHandler({\n    db,\n    getSolPrice: async () => {\n      const result = await fetchSolPrice();\n      return result?.price ?? null;\n    },\n  }),\n);\n\n// Line 235-238\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.CRATE_DROP,\n  createCrateDropHandler({ db }),\n);\n\n// Line 239-242\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT,\n  createCrateSolPayoutHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\n```\n\n#### Route Mounting:\n\n**Challenge Routes** (Lines 290-295):\n- Path: `/challenges`\n- Auth: JWT required\n- `createChallengeRoutes({ db })`\n\n**Points Routes** (Lines 297-302):\n- Path: `/points`\n- Auth: JWT required\n- `createPointsRoutes({ db })`\n\n**Crate Routes** (Lines 304-309):\n- Path: `/crates`\n- Auth: JWT required\n- `createCrateRoutes({ db })`\n\n**Dogpile Routes** (Line 312):\n- Path: `/dogpile`\n- Auth: Public (no auth required)\n- `createDogpileRoutes({ db })`\n\n**Admin Routes** (Lines 315-318):\n- Path: `/admin`\n- Auth: X-Admin-Key header required\n- `createAdminRoutes({ db, adminApiKey: config.adminApiKey })`\n- Conditional on `config.adminApiKey` being set\n\n**Worker Startup** (Lines 244-256):\n- Dogpile status worker: `createDogpileWorker({ db, pollIntervalMs: 10_000 })` (line 245)\n- Event queue worker: `createEventWorker(sql, { pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs })` (line 250)\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe challenge engine is a fully integrated event-driven system where:\n1. Game settlement (coinflip, lord, closecall) emits `game.settled` events\n2. The `game.settled` handler orchestrates challenge progress evaluation via pure adapters\n3. On challenge completion, reward intents are emitted (points, crate)\n4. The points-grant handler applies Dogpile multipliers from the active dogpile_events\n5. The crate-drop handler manages SOL and points crate rolls\n6. Completion bonuses are checked and awarded atomically within transactions\n7. Onboarding challenges auto-chain when prerequisite challenges complete\n8. All handlers are registered with the event queue and processed asynchronously\n9. Routes provide player-facing endpoints for challenges, points, and crates, plus admin endpoints for configuration"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b2d95d4b-db07-48d6-a5bf-2a0c1dc6d3ff","uuid":"9f82e4eb-0bba-4207-abfc-473052e5932e","timestamp":"2026-04-04T07:59:07.297Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need you to inventory the challenge engine implementation in the backend codebase. This is a RESEARCH task only - do not write any files.\n\nSpecifically, I need you to find and report:\n\n1. **Event types** in `backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts` - list all event type constants\n2. **Event handlers** in `backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/` - list all files and their exported functions with line numbers\n3. **Routes** in `backend/services/backend/src/routes/` - list all route files, exported functions, and the HTTP endpoints they define (with line numbers)\n4. **Workers** in `backend/services/backend/src/worker/` - list all files that emit game.settled events or handle dogpile\n5. **Handler registration** in `backend/services/backend/sr