{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019CPHdDURRQi3EMkADzuhYS","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me summarize all my findings in a comprehensive report.\n\n## Gap Analysis Report\n\nBased on my thorough review of the implementation, here are my findings for each verification point:\n\n### 1. **settle-tx.ts: `game.settled` event emission within transaction (Coinflip)**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`\n**Lines:** 354-467\n**Finding:** ✅ COMPLIANT. The `emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.GAME_SETTLED, ...)` call at line 442 is WITHIN the `db.withTransaction()` block (lines 354-467). All settlement DB writes, referral earnings, and event emission happen atomically inside the same transaction for coinflip.\n\n### 2. **settle-tx.ts: `game.settled` event emission within transaction (Lord)**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`\n**Lines:** 620-744\n**Finding:** ✅ COMPLIANT. The `emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.GAME_SETTLED, ...)` call at line 729 is WITHIN the `db.withTransaction()` block (lines 620-744). Lord settlement is atomic.\n\n### 3. **closecall-clock.ts: `game.settled` event emission within transaction**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts`\n**Lines:** 444-621\n**Finding:** ✅ COMPLIANT. The `emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.GAME_SETTLED, ...)` call at line 611 is WITHIN the `db.withTransaction()` block (lines 444-621). Close Call settlement is atomic.\n\n### 4. **game-settled.ts: Quest eligibility check BEFORE processing**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/game-settled.ts`\n**Lines:** 160-301, with quest check at lines 171-177\n**Finding:** ✅ COMPLIANT. The `questEligible(player)` check occurs at line 171, which is BEFORE any challenge progress evaluation (line 180), points grant (line 277), or crate drop (line 287). Refunded games (isWinner === null) are skipped entirely. Per-player try/catch is implemented at lines 169-300.\n\n### 5. **points-grant.ts: Both wager-based AND pre-calculated grants**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/points-grant.ts`\n**Lines:** 92-179\n**Finding:** ✅ COMPLIANT. Handler handles both grant types:\n  - **Wager-based (lines 107-142):** Converts lamports → USD (via SOL price) → points, applies Dogpile multiplier\n  - **Pre-calculated (lines 144-150):** Handles `crate_points`, `challenge_completed`, `bonus_completed` via the `amount` field directly\n\n### 6. **crate-drop.ts: SELECT...FOR UPDATE on reward_pool + CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT emission**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/crate-drop.ts`\n**Lines:** 35-48 (lock), 186 (emit CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT)\n**Finding:** ✅ COMPLIANT. \n  - Lock: `SELECT ... FROM reward_pool WHERE id = 1 FOR UPDATE` at lines 38-42\n  - SOL Payout Event: `emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT, ...)` at line 186 for SOL crates\n\n### 7. **challenges.ts: GET /challenges/mine returns onboarding section with locked: boolean**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/challenges.ts`\n**Lines:** 423-457\n**Finding:** ✅ COMPLIANT. \n  - Lines 423-457 build the `onboarding` object\n  - Line 434: Returns `null` if all steps completed (allCompleted === true)\n  - Line 439: Each step includes `locked: boolean` (set to `!isAssigned`)\n  - Line 455: Otherwise returns `{ steps, completed: false }`\n\n### 8. **challenges.ts: GET /mine/history uses cursor-based pagination**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/challenges.ts`\n**Lines:** 497-559\n**Finding:** ✅ COMPLIANT. Uses cursor-based pagination:\n  - Line 503: Accepts `cursor` query param\n  - Lines 507-509: Applies cursor filter (`id < cursor`)\n  - Line 549: Calculates `nextCursor` from last item's ID if result